If you're making the emulator, you could tell what time the writes are happening, and maybe print the scanline and pixel number to stdout or a textbox every time there's a write to $2005 or $2006.<br />Then compare it against another emulator with a debugger, so you can see if yours is different.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Thu Jun 23, 2011 1:38 pm</p><hr />
